set the cmake install interface directories on the library targets (#196) the cmake package gets imported targets generated for use by API consumers.

so they can do

```
target_link_libraries(myapp KDSoap::kdsoap)
```

in their cmake code and because KDSoap::kdsoap is an imported target cmake
automatically knows where to find the library. alas, since we didn't
set an interface directory cmake did not know where to find the relevant
headers.
this isn't a problem so long as they are in one of the standard search
paths (e.g. /usr/include), but when the are installed elsewhere (e.g.
/opt/kdsoap/include) they will not be found.

by explicitly setting the INSTALL_INTERFACE to INSTALL_INCLUDE_DIR the
generated KDSoapTargets.cmake will set the relevant path on the target
and thus allow idiomatic use of the imported target without having to
mess with include dirs manually.

Add support for timing out requests Default 30 minutes, configurable with KDSoapClientInterface::setTimeout().

This is useful because some systems even have 3 hours as TCP timeout,
and QNetworkAccessManager isn't very good at handling timeouts anyway.

Especially blocking calls should really not block for 30 minutes,
applications can now set a much smaller timeout value.

bug where the fault element name wasn't set.

One of the symptoms was that KDSoapMessage::toXml() would assert
because name().isEmpty().

KDSoapServer: Fix for Qt without SSL compiled in The compilation of KDSoap was failing if Qt is build without SSL
enabled. The define QT_NO_OPENSSL is set in the
QtNetwork/qtnetwork-config.h header, which is not included before the
define is used. QTcpSocket will load header for us and was already
always included (either directly or via QSslSocket).

kdwsdl2cpp: Added import-path argument to search for files locally Normally files needed by kdwsdl2cpp are downloaded. This patch adds an
option to search for the files locally. This increases the compilation
speed and improved reproducibility.
When the import-path is supplied, the needed files (for example schemas)
are search at: <importpath>/<URL-host>/<URL-path>
If the file is not found at the import path, then it will be downloaded
as it normally would.
For example the schema http://www.w3.org/2001/xml.xsd with the option
"-import-path /tmp" will be search at /tmp/www.w3.org/2001/xml.xsd.

Improve detection of soap fault in http response The soap 1.2 spec states that soap faults of type env:Sender should have
http status code 400 Bad request. The previous code assumed that all
soap error have status code 500 (which is true for soap 1.1). This
change tries to find a soap fault in the response data (regardless of
the http status code) and will return that if available. Else it will
fallback to the generic fault based on the response error.

Fix error code when authentication failed If no credentials is available or if the credentials are incorrect,
then the real error message is hidden behind the cancellation of the
http call. By not aborting the call, the error state will stay
QNetworkReply::AuthenticationRequiredError. This will result is KDSoap
generating a SoapFault containing the correct error message.
This way the application can detect the error and ask the user for
correct credentials.

Implement support for substitution groups. Details:

  <xs:element name="Path" abstract="true" type="t:BasePathToElementType"/>
  <xs:element name="FieldURI" type="t:PathToUnindexedFieldType" substitutionGroup="t:Path"/>
  <xs:element name="IndexedFieldURI" type="t:PathToIndexedFieldType" substitutionGroup="t:Path" />
  <xs:element name="ExtendedFieldURI" type="t:PathToExtendedFieldType" substitutionGroup="t:Path"/>

  <!-- Arrays of paths -->
  <xs:complexType name="NonEmptyArrayOfPathsToElementType">
    <xs:choice maxOccurs ="unbounded">
      <xs:element ref="t:Path"/>
    </xs:choice>
  </xs:complexType>

Generates these classes as expected:
 class T__BasePathToElementType {...};
 class T__PathToIndexedFieldType : public T__BasePathToElementType {...};
 class T__PathToUnindexedFieldType : public T__BasePathToElementType {...};
... all with virtual KDSoapValue serialize( const QString& valueName ) const;

The bug:
 this generated code in T__NonEmptyArrayOfPathsToElementType::serialize:
   KDSoapValue _valuePath(d_ptr->mPath.at(i)->serialize("Path"));// converter_complextype.cpp:291
   where "Path" was hardcoded, instead of being the type-dependent element name.

Solution:
1) At parsing time:
in XSDType add a QName substitutionElementName getter+setter,
and while parsing the XSD and encountering a substitutionGroup attribute, fill this in the associated type.
(If the same type has more than one element name associated, they are aliases, any one will do.)

2) At code generation time:
Add a virtual method QString _kd_substitutionElementName() in types used by elements with substitutions.

Generate this code in T__NonEmptyArrayOfPathsToElementType:
 baseClass->serialize(baseClass->substitutionElementName())

Fix conflict between complex type "Foo" and anonymous complex type "foo" (named after the element <foo>), both leading to a C++ class "Foo".
This is done in multiple steps:
1) mark anonymous complex types as such
2) detect conflicts in TypeCollector, and mark the lowercase type as
conflicting
3) append a suffix (e.g. "Element", for anonymous types) to the C++ class
name, in TypeMap::addSchemaTypes.
This leaves the QName unchanged (so that type lookups work), and only
renames anonymous types in case of conflicts, to avoid breaking source
compatibility (and expectatiions) for all other anonymous types.

If we have QT_FATAL_WARNINGS defined this will baulk. In my local checkout I have modifed this to qDebug() line rather than a call to the message handler. The code disambiguateis currently inline within cleanupUnusedTypes() to test functionality. There is a TODO to refactor this out along with the functionality of the cleanupUnusedTypes(). So we'll have a base class that builds a KWSDL object and then another process class which offers cleanupUnusedTypes() and disambiguate() given a KWSDL object.

KDSDEV-15 QName c'tors now initialise member data as previously there was a potential to use QName::prefix() with an uninitialised mPrefix. Also the second c'tor has been extended to cope with the potential that the second argument could also contain a prefix. It now uses QName::parse() to "do the right thing" - that is - if the prefix is present initialise mPrefix and populate mLocalName as per usual. The is no longer a need for the assert as that is handled in QName::parse().

Make delayed response handling per socket. There can be multiple client connections, where the old approach broke in the following scenario: - Request A arrives on Socket 1. request is processed delayed, the server object's delayedResponse flag is set. - Request B arrives on Socket 2 which is processed synchronously. The reply is then not sent, as delayedResponse is still set (because A's response is pending). When A is processed, the delayed response is sent correctly, but B's response is lost. Moving the delayedResponse flag into the socket avoids this problem. git-svn-id: svn+ssh://svn.kdab.com/home/SVN-klaralv/products/kdsoap/trunk@42439 c66179b2-ff0d-0410-8aef-1b1a91e65cfa

Rework server-side code generation to be a subclass of KDSoapServerObjectInterface, triggered with "-server" command-line argument. Finally understood the RPC and Document styles of SOAP, and fixed many things in the implementation:
- Let KDSoapClientInterface know the style, to not wrap the message with <method> in Document style,
  but use the message name() instead. Behavior is preserved with 1.0 (default is RPC).
- Serialize to the proper element name, in document mode, not to the part name.
- Fix wsdl_document unittest to use document style properly (<part element="...">), and adapt
  the calling code accordingly.
- Fix complex type serialization to also serialize "empty" elements, so that the xml element is
  actually written out, necessary for calling a no-argument method in document style.

Fixing the problems with groupwise.wsdl, step 8: support for XML attributes. This needed a major redesign of KDSoapValue/KDSoapValueList.
KDSoapValue can now hold both a value, and children (elements and attributes, in a KDSoapValueList)
This reduces the amount of qvariant-to-KDSoapValueList conversions too.

Added unittests for attributes.
Splitted out unittests based on sugarcrm.wsdl so that "builtinhttp" can remain dynamic-only.
Added code for sending, parsing, and serializing+deserializing (in the wsdl compiler) xml attributes.

This commit also makes the sending of xsi:type more logical: 1) only sent in EncodedUse mode, even for basic types,
2) passed as parameter rather than guessed, which sends better type names for xmlschema-defined specializations of basic types.
